The om-utility codes are provided for creating convenient summaries (omp-summary/ 
directory) of the optical model database (om-parameter-u.dat) and for adding or
deleting potentials from the library (add-omp/ directory).

The om-get directory contains a retrieval code and associated files that
can be used to produce inputs for the SCAT2000, ECIS06 and OPTMAN optical model
codes from the phenomenological OMP libraries.  

The om-microscopic directory contains a microscopic optical model code from
Bruyeres-le-Chatel, together with complete description of the contents and how
to use the code.
 
The om-alpha/ directory contains two codes By Kumar et al [1] and Demetriou et al [2] 
for obtaining global alpha-particle potentials. 

[1] A. Kumar and S. Kailas, Nucl. Phys. A776 (2006) 105-117
[2] P. Demetriou, C. Grama and S. Goriely, Nucl. Phys. A707 (2002) 253-276



